article.headline: Bradley 90, Evansville 62
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Patrick O'Bryant scored 15 points on 6-of-7 shooting Saturday, leading Bradley to a 90-62 win over Evansville. O'Bryant added five rebounds, three assists and six blocks for the Braves (9-6, 3-4 Missouri Valley), who had five players score in double figures. Daniel Ruffin scored 15 and dished out seven assists. Tony Bennett scored 12, while Zach Andrews and Lawrence Wright each added 10. The Braves led 44-29 at halftime. Matt Webster led the way for Evansville (5-9, 1-5), scoring 19 points and grabbing seven rebounds. Shy Ely added 16 for the Purple Aces. But Evansville shot only 35 percent from the field in the loss, including connecting on just three of 18 3-point attempts. Bradley, meanwhile, shot 57 percent from the field and converted six of 13 3-pointers.
